  "statements": [
    {
      "issue": "housing",
      "sourceUrl": "https://www.scottwiener.com/priorities",
      "text": "Scott is a nationally renowned leader on housing, authoring California's most consequential streamlining laws resulting in the construction of tens of thousands of homes — including 3,000+ below market rate, affordable homes in San Francisco."
    },
    {
      "issue": "healthcare",
      "sourceUrl": "https://www.scottwiener.com/priorities",
      "text": "We need Medicare for All. And until we get there, Scott will tackle healthcare affordability in Congress just like he has in the Legislature: by capping insulin at $35/month, forcing insurance companies to cover mental healthcare, reducing prior authorizations, lowering prescription drug prices, and working to reverse Trump's cuts to Medicaid and the Affordable Care Act."
    },
    {
      "issue": "climate",
      "sourceUrl": "https://www.scottwiener.com/priorities",
      "text": "Named a TIME100 Climate Champion, Scott passed a first-in-the-nation law requiring large corporations to disclose their carbon emissions."
    },
    {
      "issue": "immigration",
      "sourceUrl": "https://www.scottwiener.com/priorities",
      "text": "When masked agents began disappearing people off the streets, Scott passed first-in-the-nation legislation to make it illegal for ICE to wear masks, and he is now working to end impunity for ICE by allowing you to sue them when they violate your rights — it's currently nearly impossible to sue them under federal law."
    }
  ],
